stories.title: England v Australia, Edgbaston
stories.subTitle: The NatWest Series 2005
stories.summary: England v Australia, Edgbaston, NatWest Series 2005

stories.title: Jones promises England will not back down
stories.subTitle: The storm from the heated clash
stories.summary: Simon Jones has promised Australia there will be no let-up from England when it comes to aggressive cricket this season after being involved in a fiery exchange in the last one-dayer at Edgbaston.

stories.title: Vaughan defends aggressive England
stories.subTitle: England v Australia, NatWest Series, Edgbaston
stories.summary: Michael Vaughan defended his team following the unsavoury scenes during the washed-out one-day international at Edgbaston

stories.title: Stormy end to a stormy match
stories.subTitle: England v Australia, NatWest Series, Edgbaston
stories.summary: There were fireworks aplenty as Australia raced to 46 for 2 from their first ten overs

stories.title: Tempers rise in heated kitchen
stories.subTitle: England v Australia, NatWest Series, Edgbaston
stories.summary: This summer has been simmering, and though the late-evening thunderstorm freshened the air, the cricket at Edgbaston was still very heated
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Andrew McGlashan
